    {
      "instruction": "<p>Flake the <strong>cooked basa</strong> into the crushed<strong> </strong>potatoes, add your<strong> chipotle paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> </strong>1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> then mix</p><p>Divide the mixture into 2 per person<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and shape into fishcakes, then press into the <strong>smoky</strong> <strong>breadcrumbs </strong>firmly to evenly coat – these are your <strong>smoky chipotle fishcakes</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>smoky chipotle fishcakes </strong>to a<strong> tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!), drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and put in the oven for 15-20 min or until golden</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
